together parents, and teachers,

00:20:44.780 --> 00:20:48.470
students, administrators,
along with the D.C. Commission

00:20:48.470 --> 00:20:49.970
and the Kennedy Center.

00:20:49.970 --> 00:20:53.900
To develop an arts education
agenda for Washington, D.C.,

00:20:53.900 --> 00:20:56.570
as well as specific
measurable goals

00:20:56.570 --> 00:20:59.560
for how the agenda
will be achieved.

00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:04.440
We envision a day when all
communities make arts education

00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:07.280
a priority, just
as D.C. is doing.

00:21:07.280 --> 00:21:10.070
And over the past five
decades, the National Endowment

00:21:10.070 --> 00:21:13.130
for the Arts has
invested 244 million

00:21:13.130 --> 00:21:16.650
in arts education projects
across the United States,

00:21:16.650 --> 00:21:19.870
and these projects range
from in-school performances

00:21:19.870 --> 00:21:21.880
and artist residencies.

00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:24.480
Afterschool arts
programs for students,

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:26.830
professional development
for teachers,

00:21:26.830 --> 00:21:29.840
collective impact projects such
as the one I've just mentioned

00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:31.140
with the D.C. Arts

00:21:31.140 --> 00:21:33.470
and Humanities Education
Collaborative collective

00:21:33.470 --> 00:21:35.050
impact group.

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:40.160
We must thrive, and we must
strive to empower every child

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:43.820
in this country with an
excellent arts education.

00:21:43.820 --> 00:21:47.600
Forty percent of our arts
education grants are awarded

00:21:47.600 --> 00:21:50.650
to organizations in
high-poverty communities,

00:21:50.650 --> 00:21:55.500
and we're also launching a
statewide data infrastructure

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:58.980
