or to sing can help
disadvantaged children

00:44:09.250 --> 00:44:11.430
strengthen their reading
and language skills,

00:44:11.430 --> 00:44:13.790
which may reduce
academic achievement gaps.

00:44:13.790 --> 00:44:16.750
These findings involved hundreds
of children participating

00:44:16.750 --> 00:44:19.750
in musical training
programs in both Chicago

00:44:19.750 --> 00:44:21.970
and Los Angeles public schools.

00:44:21.970 --> 00:44:24.060
The positive role that
musical training can have

00:44:24.060 --> 00:44:28.560
for youth living in impoverished
areas was presented by Dr. Kraus

00:44:28.560 --> 00:44:31.930
in 2014, at the American
Psychological Association's

00:44:31.930 --> 00:44:33.240
annual convention.

00:44:33.240 --> 00:44:34.810
Kraus's research concluded

00:44:34.810 --> 00:44:37.800
that musical training can
enhance the way children's

00:44:37.800 --> 00:44:43.190
nervous systems process sounds
in busy or chaotic environments,

00:44:43.190 --> 00:44:45.490
like a classroom,
or a playground.

00:44:45.490 --> 00:44:48.570
After just two years
of musical training --

00:44:48.570 --> 00:44:51.510
not one, because she looked
at one and also two years.

00:44:51.510 --> 00:44:54.010
After two years of
musical training,

00:44:54.010 --> 00:44:58.500
the children's brain
responses to sounds were faster

00:44:58.500 --> 00:45:02.480
and more precise than in
students who had other types

00:45:02.480 --> 00:45:03.780
of enrichment classes.

00:45:03.780 --> 00:45:06.970
So this was not just
a comparison

00:45:06.970 --> 00:45:08.850
of music classes to nothing.

00:45:08.850 --> 00:45:10.810
The improved neural
function caused

00:45:10.810 --> 00:45:13.490
by music training may
lead to enhanced memory

00:45:13.490 --> 00:45:16.880
and attention span, which in
turn can make it easier for kids

00:45:16.880 --> 00:45:18.630
to stay focused in the classroom

00:45:18.630 --> 00:45:20.850
and improve their
communication skills.

00:45:20.850 --> 00:45:23.220
Other separate studies
over the last five

00:45:23.220 --> 00:45:27.530
to six years have shown
that arithmetic performance,

00:45:27.530 --> 00:45:30.730
achievement in verbal
skills, language learning,

00:45:30.730 --> 00:45:33.480
and even second, foreign
language acquisition,

00:45:33.480 --> 00:45:35.740
which I would argue is
increasingly important

00:45:35.740 --> 00:45:38.170
in our globalized world.

00:45:38.170 --> 00:45:41.080
That actually can be
made easier by music.

00:45:41.080 --> 00:45:45.200
You heard before that music
is a language all its own.

00:45:45.200 --> 00:45:47.280
Well, there's actually
now neural --

00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:49.680
anatomical neurobiological
truth to that.

00:45:49.680 --> 00:45:54.020
And we know that with each
additional language acquired,

00:45:54.020 --> 00:45:57.290
it becomes easier to acquire
the subsequent language,

00:45:57.290 --> 00:45:59.810
even if it's not
connected in any way

00:45:59.810 --> 00:46:01.290
to the languages
you already know.

00:46:01.290 --> 00:46:05.220
So research has shown that there
are differences in the brains

00:46:05.220 --> 00:46:07.600
of children raised in
impoverished environments

00:46:07.600 --> 00:46:09.420
that affect their
ability to learn.

00:46:09.420 --> 00:46:12.220
While more affluent students
do better in school than kids

00:46:12.220 --> 00:46:15.410
from lower-income backgrounds,
we are starting to find

00:46:15.410 --> 00:46:18.040
that musical training can
alter the nervous system

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:23.430
to create a better learner and
help offset this academic gap.

00:46:23.430 --> 00:46:27.040
And so I'm happy to talk
more, but I want to make sure

00:46:27.040 --> 00:46:29.480
that other panelists
have enough time.

00:46:29.480 --> 00:46:35.820
So I just want to conclude by
saying that evidence is mounting

00:46:35.820 --> 00:46:37.520
that musical training
boosts brain power

00:46:37.520 --> 00:46:40.010
and cognitive function
in children and adults.

00:46:40.010 --> 00:46:41.720
Neural enhancements
that are gained

00:46:41.720 --> 00:46:43.020
through musical training early

00:46:43.020 --> 00:46:47.490
in life can extend throughout
the lifespan and into old age.

00:46:47.490 --> 00:46:50.360
And hopefully, these
findings can inspire parents

00:46:50.360 --> 00:46:53.560
and policymakers to advocate
for musical training in school

00:46:53.560 --> 00:46:57.170
as an enjoyable and fulfilling
outlet that also has the power

00:46:57.170 --> 00:47:00.390
to boost our brain strength
and improve reading,

00:47:00.390 --> 00:47:01.690
writing, and arithmetic.

00:47:01.690 --> 00:47:05.100
There are data actually that
need to be expanded upon

00:47:05.100 --> 00:47:09.060
that all aspects of the SAT
are improved by between 20

00:47:09.060 --> 00:47:11.780
to 30 points when comparing kids

00:47:11.780 --> 00:47:14.680
who have had music classes
regularly throughout school

00:47:14.680 --> 00:47:15.980
to those who have not.

00:47:15.980 --> 00:47:19.030
So it seems that musical
training keeps our brain --

00:47:19.030 --> 00:47:21.310
helps keep our brain
sharp as we age

00:47:21.310 --> 00:47:23.670
and could be an integral part
of rehabilitative programs

00:47:23.670 --> 00:47:27.540
for older adults, as well,
coping with cognitive decline.

00:47:27.540 --> 00:47:28.840
All right.

