after a national search

00:52:50.210 --> 00:52:52.080
for a new director just
this past September.

00:52:52.080 --> 00:52:53.960
So I'm pretty new to this role.

00:52:53.960 --> 00:52:56.210
Obviously, I'm not
new to the arts.

00:52:56.210 --> 00:53:00.590
But Dance Place, in addition
to being a presenting theater

00:53:00.590 --> 00:53:04.780
that hosts over 45 weekends
of performances each year

00:53:04.780 --> 00:53:07.580
from international,
national, and area companies,

00:53:07.580 --> 00:53:10.240
and having a school, and having
youth enrichment programs,

00:53:10.240 --> 00:53:12.490
has been an anchor
in our neighborhood.

00:53:12.490 --> 00:53:17.260
When Carla and her board at the
time bought their building in --

00:53:17.260 --> 00:53:22.250
31 years ago, it became
kind of a galvanizing force

00:53:22.250 --> 00:53:23.550
for that neighborhood.

00:53:23.550 --> 00:53:25.210
And we all recognize
the problems

00:53:25.210 --> 00:53:27.370
that come with gentrification.

00:53:27.370 --> 00:53:28.690
We've been pretty fortunate

00:53:28.690 --> 00:53:30.110
in the Brookland/Edgewood
neighborhood

00:53:30.110 --> 00:53:32.840
because of a history
of high home ownership

00:53:32.840 --> 00:53:35.950
in that neighborhood, and as
well as some pockets of land

00:53:35.950 --> 00:53:38.630
