01:43:33.270 --> 01:43:34.570
&gt;&gt; Dr. Alexander
Panteyat: Absolutely.

01:43:34.570 --> 01:43:37.640
So there are already a number
of studies that indicated

01:43:37.640 --> 01:43:43.240
that group music-making can be
incredibly pro-social for kids

01:43:43.240 --> 01:43:45.790
on the autism spectrum.

01:43:45.790 --> 01:43:50.500
And your -- the timing of your
question for me is very apt.

01:43:50.500 --> 01:43:53.530
I am exploring a research
study at Johns Hopkins,

01:43:53.530 --> 01:43:57.940
my institution, as we speak with
the Kennedy Krieger Institute

01:43:57.940 --> 01:43:59.840
and several other partners.

01:43:59.840 --> 01:44:02.250
So we have an interested
music therapist,

01:44:02.250 --> 01:44:04.420
and we are actively
exploring that now.

01:44:04.420 --> 01:44:09.230
Until now, my work as a movement
disorders neurologist has

01:44:09.230 --> 01:44:12.990
focused on the other end
of the spectrum, aging.

01:44:12.990 --> 01:44:17.070
So I've done a study called
Parkinsonics using group

01:44:17.070 --> 01:44:20.500
choir-based singing to
improve communication --

01:44:20.500 --> 01:44:23.840
get the voice louder and clearer
in patients with Parkinson's,

01:44:23.840 --> 01:44:25.470
and we're submitting
that for publication

01:44:25.470 --> 01:44:26.770
in the next few weeks.

01:44:26.770 --> 01:44:29.250
And just to give
everybody a broader context,

01:44:29.250 --> 01:44:33.350
I've been very fortunate
to help establish and lead

01:44:33.350 --> 01:44:36.690
at Johns Hopkins our Center for
Music in Medicine where we seek

01:44:36.690 --> 01:44:41.140
to make music and rhythm an
integral part of healing illness

01:44:41.140 --> 01:44:43.930
across the age spectrum.

01:44:43.930 --> 01:44:45.230
&gt;&gt; Mario Rossero: Great.

01:44:45.230 --> 01:44:46.990
And you know, it's interesting,
performing arts organizations,

01:44:46.990 --> 01:44:49.260
definitely across the District,
but across country also,

01:44:49.260 --> 01:44:51.370
are really thinking about --

01:44:51.370 --> 01:44:53.220
for performances how to
create more relaxed settings

01:44:53.220 --> 01:44:57.620
so that whether it's an
autistic child or other barrier

01:44:57.620 --> 01:44:59.510
