02:08:20.600 --> 02:08:24.450
So just to give you a context
of who we are at the University

02:08:24.450 --> 02:08:27.180
of the Arts, we're in
Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.

02:08:27.180 --> 02:08:31.340
We are a small private art
institution that houses all

02:08:31.340 --> 02:08:34.020
of the arts -- visual,
performing and creative writing.

02:08:34.020 --> 02:08:36.400
We're actually the only
university in the nation

02:08:36.400 --> 02:08:39.040
to devote ourselves
exclusively to the arts.

02:08:39.040 --> 02:08:42.680
There are 1800 students
that are studying graduate

02:08:42.680 --> 02:08:44.470
and undergraduate programs.

02:08:44.470 --> 02:08:45.940
And I represent the Dean

02:08:45.940 --> 02:08:48.000
of Continuing Studies,
so what's that?

02:08:48.000 --> 02:08:53.730
That's another 2900 students
that are the learning continuum

02:08:53.730 --> 02:08:57.380
from very young people that
do out-of-school programs

02:08:57.380 --> 02:09:00.980
on Saturdays and credit-bearing
programs in the summer

02:09:00.980 --> 02:09:02.380
for high school students.

02:09:02.380 --> 02:09:05.120
We also have enrichment
programs for adults.

02:09:05.120 --> 02:09:09.280
But we also have about a
thousand in-service K-12

02:09:09.280 --> 02:09:12.990
teachers that come to
us to study programs.

02:09:12.990 --> 02:09:15.230
The Summer Music
Studies Program --

02:09:15.230 --> 02:09:19.650
which Johanna actually teaches
in -- is part of that program.

02:09:19.650 --> 02:09:22.370
And we also have a Professional
Institute for Educators

02:09:22.370 --> 02:09:25.880
and those two, the music program

02:09:25.880 --> 02:09:29.230
and the professional institute
programs, we have non-matric

02:09:29.230 --> 02:09:32.410
and matric courses
for educators.

02:09:32.410 --> 02:09:35.590
And so in that program
is the Teaching

02:09:35.590 --> 02:09:37.200
with Primary Sources Program.

02:09:37.200 --> 02:09:39.650
And just to give you a
little bit of a history --

02:09:39.650 --> 02:09:44.320
back in 2010, we saw an
RFP for an organization

02:09:44.320 --> 02:09:47.620
to deliver opportunities
to develop curriculum

02:09:47.620 --> 02:09:51.290
and professional development
experiences for K-12 teachers.

02:09:51.290 --> 02:09:53.250
And my colleagues saw
it and said, "Anne,

02:09:53.250 --> 02:09:54.980
we have to apply for that.

02:09:54.980 --> 02:09:56.280
We're just perfect."

02:09:56.280 --> 02:09:58.300
And I said, "Yes, but
we're really at capacity.

02:09:58.300 --> 02:10:01.060
How much more can we
do with 2500 students?"

02:10:01.060 --> 02:10:03.290
And she said, "But
how can we not?"

02:10:03.290 --> 02:10:04.600
And I said, "How can we not?"

02:10:04.600 --> 02:10:06.640
And so we were thrilled
when we're selected

02:10:06.640 --> 02:10:08.860
to be part of a consortium.

02:10:08.860 --> 02:10:11.000
And what was really
exciting to learn was

02:10:11.000 --> 02:10:13.270
that the other consortium
members which were

02:10:13.270 --> 02:10:15.440
from across the United
States working in a lot

02:10:15.440 --> 02:10:17.810
of different disciplines,
a lot of them history,

02:10:17.810 --> 02:10:21.810
actually they themselves had
requested an arts-based partner

02:10:21.810 --> 02:10:24.820
because nobody in the consortium
was doing work in the arts.

02:10:24.820 --> 02:10:26.780
And they thought that
was really important.

02:10:26.780 --> 02:10:28.490
So you can -- I just -- this is

