02:10:35.540 --> 02:10:37.790
a lot of cultures
think about the past.

02:10:37.790 --> 02:10:41.240
We actually adapted as our
logo, "Look back, see further"

02:10:41.240 --> 02:10:43.130
for our work with teaching
with primary sources

02:10:43.130 --> 02:10:45.860
because we really -- that
was sort of what emerged

02:10:45.860 --> 02:10:47.160
when we're trying to think

02:10:47.160 --> 02:10:49.930
about how do we encapsulate
this work that we're doing?

02:10:49.930 --> 02:10:55.810
And so, really we set about
creating a comprehensive program

02:10:55.810 --> 02:10:59.320
where we can help educators, K
through 12 and service teachers

02:10:59.320 --> 02:11:01.740
and librarians, really figure

02:11:01.740 --> 02:11:04.830
out how they can bring the
arts into their teaching.

02:11:04.830 --> 02:11:07.290
And for us, it was a little
bit of a journey as well.

02:11:07.290 --> 02:11:09.220
So where we stand right
now, what we've developed

02:11:09.220 --> 02:11:11.300
and we give you an overview and
I'm going to sort of break it

02:11:11.300 --> 02:11:14.210
down a little bit, is
that we offer courses.

02:11:14.210 --> 02:11:16.380
They're available for
free for non-credit.

02:11:16.380 --> 02:11:18.310
We also offer three
graduate credits.

02:11:18.310 --> 02:11:21.340
And our matriculated students
can also take these programs.

02:11:21.340 --> 02:11:23.320
And we have two different types
of courses which I'll break

02:11:23.320 --> 02:11:25.810
down a little bit later
which is an overview course

02:11:25.810 --> 02:11:28.360
and discipline-specific courses.

02:11:28.360 --> 02:11:31.120
We also create some
curriculum guides that come

02:11:31.120 --> 02:11:33.940
