Then we also talk about
this wonderful tool which is

02:16:06.280 --> 02:16:09.560
in the guides that we're handing
out and online in our website.

02:16:09.560 --> 02:16:12.100
And we're -- it's
sort of this --

02:16:12.100 --> 02:16:15.660
a framework for observe,
question and reflect.

02:16:15.660 --> 02:16:16.960
And it walks you through it.

02:16:16.960 --> 02:16:19.340
And there's one specifically
for prints and photographs

02:16:19.340 --> 02:16:21.890
but there's more general
ones and we use that.

02:16:21.890 --> 02:16:25.470
We use that as an examples
and we have some --

02:16:25.470 --> 02:16:28.970
always have great lecturers
come in that talk about the arts

02:16:28.970 --> 02:16:31.670
and primary sources and
make those connections.

02:16:31.670 --> 02:16:34.520
And you know, we're in
Philadelphia so there is no lack

02:16:34.520 --> 02:16:37.090
of amazing collections.

02:16:37.090 --> 02:16:41.680
And we utilize as many
of them as possible.

