So this artist, Diane
Burko, was fascinating.

02:18:39.480 --> 02:18:41.370
For 35 years, she's
been flying all

02:18:41.370 --> 02:18:43.960
over the world photographing
climate change.

02:18:43.960 --> 02:18:45.610
She was really ahead
of her time.

02:18:45.610 --> 02:18:47.360
And she's taken those
photographs and turned them

02:18:47.360 --> 02:18:49.400
into prints and paintings
and she lectures.

02:18:49.400 --> 02:18:52.840
She's been invited to the White
House to talk about her work.

02:18:52.840 --> 02:18:58.150
And so we had all these artists
in as we also visited lots

02:18:58.150 --> 02:18:59.770
of primary source locations

02:18:59.770 --> 02:19:03.340
