overview course called City

02:19:18.290 --> 02:19:20.360
as the Primary Source and we're
looking at urban planning,

02:19:20.360 --> 02:19:22.780
architecture and cartography.

02:19:22.780 --> 02:19:27.550
And we're reaching out to
people across those disciplines

02:19:27.550 --> 02:19:29.630
to develop that curriculum.

02:19:29.630 --> 02:19:32.870
In our discipline-specific
courses, we do a deep dive in.

02:19:32.870 --> 02:19:34.250
So again, it's five days.

02:19:34.250 --> 02:19:37.120
And what that looks like is that
first day is that, you know,

02:19:37.120 --> 02:19:38.420
what's a primary source?

02:19:38.420 --> 02:19:39.720
How do we use it?

02:19:39.720 --> 02:19:41.020
What's online?

02:19:41.020 --> 02:19:42.320
What's in the collection?

02:19:42.320 --> 02:19:43.620
What's really different
about this class is

02:19:43.620 --> 02:19:47.830
that the participants will
actually study one particular

02:19:47.830 --> 02:19:51.080
discipline and they will
actually create studio projects

02:19:51.080 --> 02:19:52.380
in that discipline.

02:19:52.380 --> 02:19:54.230
So it's important to
note, they're not artists.

02:19:54.230 --> 02:19:56.550
And so they're drawing
or painting

02:19:56.550 --> 02:19:58.600
or screen printing
for the first time.

02:19:58.600 --> 02:20:00.670
And so the idea is that
they're doing projects

02:20:00.670 --> 02:20:02.130
that they could model
with their students

02:20:02.130 --> 02:20:04.950
who may not have comfort
in those disciplines.

02:20:04.950 --> 02:20:07.610
And then on day five, they
actually develop a lesson plan.

02:20:07.610 --> 02:20:08.910
They share it out.

02:20:08.910 --> 02:20:10.210
And we have an exhibition.

02:20:10.210 --> 02:20:14.380
So two courses that you can
grab these educator guides.

