02:57:03.090 --> 02:57:05.770
[Inaudible] got a mic for you.

02:57:09.280 --> 02:57:11.640
&gt;&gt; Hi. Hi everybody.

02:57:11.640 --> 02:57:12.940
Thank you so very much.

02:57:12.940 --> 02:57:15.820
This was a wonderful panel.

02:57:15.820 --> 02:57:19.140
Just a wonderful day, really.

02:57:19.140 --> 02:57:22.750
Question for you all, this is a
question that we've been talking

02:57:22.750 --> 02:57:26.110
about as a community very
recently, what does it mean

02:57:26.110 --> 02:57:30.320
to be a national organization
serving local audience?

02:57:30.320 --> 02:57:33.080
Maybe some of you
could illustrate a bit

02:57:33.080 --> 02:57:36.690
of how you're working
specifically with D.C.,

02:57:36.690 --> 02:57:38.950
family engagement,
empowerment, you know,

02:57:38.950 --> 02:57:42.240
today's conversation is about
equity, access and empowerment.

02:57:42.240 --> 02:57:45.610
How are you as [inaudible]
organizations empowering young

02:57:45.610 --> 02:57:48.400
students and their families
to take full advantage

02:57:48.400 --> 02:57:51.260
and incorporate the
amazing amenities

02:57:51.260 --> 02:57:55.980
and offerings here,
nationally, to D.C.?

02:57:55.980 --> 02:57:57.280
&gt;&gt; Lee Ann Potter:
Great question.

02:57:57.280 --> 02:58:01.930
And actually, I'm very
happy that you asked it.

02:58:01.930 --> 02:58:05.490
So story time that happens here
at the Library is not something

02:58:05.490 --> 02:58:08.070
that we live stream,
it's not something

02:58:08.070 --> 02:58:10.760
that we make a big deal out of.

02:58:10.760 --> 02:58:12.960
And like I said, one of
the reasons why I wanted

02:58:12.960 --> 02:58:15.140
to invite Sasha and
Erin to do this

02:58:15.140 --> 02:58:18.600
for this particular event was
to really stretch the reach

02:58:18.600 --> 02:58:21.310
of that program, hoping that
maybe there's an opportunity

02:58:21.310 --> 02:58:23.590
for some mimicking to go on.

02:58:23.590 --> 02:58:25.190
I know certainly that programs

02:58:25.190 --> 02:58:26.790
like that are happening
all over the country.

02:58:26.790 --> 02:58:28.100
And what we want
to be doing more

02:58:28.100 --> 02:58:31.700
of here is showcasing
some of that.

02:58:31.700 --> 02:58:33.260
As you know, we're being
live streamed today.

02:58:33.260 --> 02:58:36.530
And the opportunity to extend
the reach of programs here

02:58:36.530 --> 02:58:38.700
at the Library by using
those technologies is one

02:58:38.700 --> 02:58:40.430
of the ways we're
trying to do that.

02:58:40.430 --> 02:58:43.330
But that balance between
figuring out, are you local --

02:58:43.330 --> 02:58:44.860
are you serving a
local audience,

02:58:44.860 --> 02:58:46.400
are you serving a
national audience?

02:58:46.400 --> 02:58:49.240
I'm not sure it's neither/or,
I think it's a both/and.

02:58:49.240 --> 02:58:52.140
I think there's an
opportunity to really recognize

02:58:52.140 --> 02:58:55.670
that those local audiences,
and those -- I mean, frankly,

02:58:55.670 --> 02:58:57.060
we have a [inaudible]
here at the Library

02:58:57.060 --> 02:58:58.440
in our Young Readers Center.

02:58:58.440 --> 02:59:00.660
And some of the opportunities
that we're able

02:59:00.660 --> 02:59:03.790
to make available to those young
people, we're trying to figure

02:59:03.790 --> 02:59:06.530
out very deliberately
how do we capture this

02:59:06.530 --> 02:59:10.290
and make this available to
a much broader audience.

02:59:10.290 --> 02:59:12.310
What we've done this year,
something sort of new

02:59:12.310 --> 02:59:14.870
with that group, is
asking colleagues

02:59:14.870 --> 02:59:17.690
from around the Library to come
to each one of their meetings

02:59:17.690 --> 02:59:20.040
and share with students some
of the resources that are

02:59:20.040 --> 02:59:22.660
in their collections, so that
the kids have a better sense

02:59:22.660 --> 02:59:24.360
of the enormity of the place.

02:59:24.360 --> 02:59:27.150
And we need to do that with
a much broader audience.

02:59:27.150 --> 02:59:28.530
I mean, it's both.

02:59:28.530 --> 02:59:31.150
It's both/and.

